        "client_msg_id": "8C279175-0359-49D9-8E24-4282718DE47E",
        "text": "of course this is <https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kawaii|https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kawaii>  but it is also dangerous and powerful. the idea To transform content by representation „on the fly“ \nI could see some protocols going in this direction. \nIn this way content representation would be come even much more individualistic so finding social coherence could be even more harder than the loss of movie :movie_camera: culture. But also other things could become more easy or even resilient. \nAs I pointed out above, we lack tools :hammer_and_wrench:- also as in methods, practices, to better reflect on changes to culture. \nI guess we are back to slowing down , McLuhan and WuWei :sweat_smile:\nAnother dramatic loss i noticed was the loss of fairy tales - märchen. It’s quite an advanced technology but WHO in society cares for that ?\nThe (also but not only) technological push towards acceleration also is leading to gigantic misunderstandings in communication. Some people call this the meaning crisis. ",
